All technical documentation is collected in articles, which are organized in categories and subcategories depending on the platform component or general topic they relate to. You can access these articles by clicking the ![](data:image/png;base64,)   [**Browse all articles**](https://docs.doxee.com/docs) button on the home page or the **Documentation** button in the top menu bar. Both lead to the first article in the navigation tree. You can expand and collapse categories in the navigation tree to find a specific article, or use the search and filter functions.

Doxee PlatformÂ® Documentation is organized into the following main categories:

![](data:image/png;base64,)Left navigation panel

- [**Getting started**](/doxee-platform/docs/getting-started)**:** General information about the product, points of contact, and navigation of documentation

- [**Product updates**](/doxee-platform/docs/product-updates)**:** Release notes and product roadmap

- [**Product guides**](/doxee-platform/docs/user-guides)**:** Full product documentation organized by component and release version, if applicable, including troubleshooting, best practices, installation, and migration guides
